cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for unsupervised domain adaptation in computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new metric and an end-to-end training strategy, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves designing a model architecture and optimizing the metric, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing tasks, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves experiments on real-world benchmarks, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
